{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KEWh1vUhKzcLGqmmE4Lh1f","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Book Language\n2\t\n3\tThe **Book language** is the domain-specific language in which every agent's source (\"book\") is written. It is designed to be human-readable while expressing the full behavior of an agent — its \"soul\". This spec covers the language as the Agents Server consumes it; the authoritative end-user reference is generated by the server itself and served at `GET /api/docs/book-language.md` (with `GET /api/docs/book.md` as a backward-compatible alias). A compatible server MUST serve this documentation, generated from its commitment registry.\n4\t\n5\t## Source structure\n6\t\n7\t```book\n8\tAgent Name\n9\t\n10\tPERSONA You are a helpful assistant that helps with cooking recipes.\n11\tRULE Answer only questions about cooking.\n12\tKNOWLEDGE https://example.com/recipes.pdf\n13\tUSE SEARCH ENGINE Search only in French.\n14\tMETA IMAGE https://example.com/avatar.png\n15\t```\n16\t\n17\t-   **Line 1** is the agent name. When missing/empty, a default name is derived.\n18\t-   A **commitment** starts with a recognized keyword at the beginning of a line and extends until the next commitment keyword or end of file (so a commitment's content may span multiple lines).\n19\t-   The general pattern is `<KEYWORD> <content>`, e.g. `PERSONA You are…`, `USE SEARCH ENGINE Search only in French.`\n20\t-   Text that belongs to no commitment is free-form persona text (part of the system-message composition).\n21\t-   **Parameters** may appear anywhere in content: `@ParameterName` (single word) or `{parameter name}` / `{parameterName: description}`. They are substituted from prompt parameters at execution time.\n22\t-   **Agent references** in commitment content use curly braces around an agent name or URL, e.g. `TEAM You can talk to {Criminal lawyer} and {https://other-server/agents/xyz}`.\n23\t\n24\t## Two-stage parsing\n25\t\n26\tA compatible implementation MUST provide both stages with the following division of labor:\n27\t\n28\t1. **`parseAgentSource` (synchronous, lightweight)** — extracts the [agent profile](agents.md#agent-profile) (name, hash, persona description, initial message, `meta` map, links, parameters, capabilities, samples, knowledge sources). It recognizes commitments syntactically, never performs I/O, and is used everywhere a profile is needed cheaply (listings, headers, routing).\n29\t2. **`createAgentModelRequirements` (asynchronous)** — compiles the source into **agent model requirements** by applying each commitment definition in order. This may perform I/O (resolving referenced agents, knowledge indexing). Output shape:\n30\t    -   `systemMessage` — the composed system prompt;\n31\t    -   `userMessageSuffix` — optional text appended to user prompts;\n32\t    -   `modelName` (and optional `temperature` and other model parameters);\n33\t    -   `tools` — LLM tool definitions contributed by `USE …`/`TEAM`/`ACTION` commitments.\n34\t\n35\tThe server caches the compiled requirements per `agentHash` (`Agent.preparedModelRequirements`, see [Preparation and caching](agents/preparation-and-caching.md)) and exposes them for debugging via the [model-requirements API](api/public-agent-api.md#model-requirements).\n36\t\n37\t## Commitment registry\n38\t\n39\tThe commitment registry is the single source of truth for the language. Keywords are case-insensitive per definition below; singular/plural forms and listed aliases are equivalent. A compatible implementation MUST support:\n40\t\n41\t| Commitment (aliases)                                   | Effect                                                                                                                                        |\n42\t| ------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n43\t| `PERSONA` / `PERSONAE`                                   | Describes who the agent is; contributes to the system message (legacy fallback for the profile description).                                    |\n44\t| `GOAL` / `GOALS`                                         | The agent's objective; the last one becomes the profile `personaDescription`.                                                                   |\n45\t| `KNOWLEDGE`                                              | Attaches a knowledge source (URL, file) or inline knowledge; sources are indexed for retrieval (see [Preparation](agents/preparation-and-caching.md#knowledge-indexing)). |\n46\t| `MEMORY` / `MEMORIES`                                    | Enables [user memory](users/memory.md) behavior.                                                                                                |\n47\t| `RULE` / `RULES`                                         | Hard behavioral constraint in the system message.                                                                                               |\n48\t| `STYLE` / `STYLES`                                       | Writing style instructions.                                                                                                                     |\n49\t| `LANGUAGE` / `LANGUAGES`                                 | Response language constraint.                                                                                                                   |\n50\t| `WRITING SAMPLE` / `WRITING RULES`                       | Style-by-example instructions.                                                                                                                  |\n51\t| `SAMPLE` / `EXAMPLE`                                     | Example conversations (question/answer pairs surfaced in the profile).                                                                          |\n52\t| `FORMAT` / `FORMATS`                                     | Output format constraints.                                                                                                                      |\n53\t| `TEMPLATE` / `TEMPLATES`                                 | Response templates.                                                                                                                             |\n54\t| `FROM`                                                   | Inheritance from a parent agent (see [Inheritance and imports](agents/inheritance-and-imports.md)). `FROM VOID` disables the implicit ancestor. |\n55\t| `IMPORT` / `IMPORTS`                                     | Textual inclusion of another agent's source.                                                                                                    |\n56\t| `MODEL` / `MODELS`                                       | Selects the LLM (and parameters like temperature).                                                                                              |\n57\t| `ACTION` / `ACTIONS`                                     | Declares actions the agent can perform (tool-like).                                                                                             |\n58\t| `COMPONENT`                                              | Declares UI components the agent may render.                                                                                                    |\n59\t| `META <TYPE> <content>`                                  | Generic metadata; later same-type entries override earlier. Recognized types below.                                                             |\n60\t| `META IMAGE` (`IMAGE`)                                   | Avatar/profile image URL (see [Avatars](agents/avatars-and-visuals.md)).                                                                        |\n61\t| `META AVATAR`, `META VISUAL`                             | Built-in avatar visual identifier.                                                                                                              |\n62\t| `META COLOR` (`COLOR`), `META FONT` (`FONT`)             | Brand color / font of the agent page.                                                                                                           |\n63\t| `META LINK`                                              | Related links shown on the profile.                                                                                                             |\n64\t| `META DOMAIN` (`DOMAIN`)                                 | Custom domain claim for the agent (see [Servers and multi-tenancy](servers-and-multi-tenancy.md#custom-domains)).                                |\n65\t| `META DISCLAIMER`                                        | Markdown disclaimer users must accept before chatting (enforced; see [Public agent API](api/public-agent-api.md#meta-disclaimer)).               |\n66\t| `META INPUT PLACEHOLDER`                                 | Placeholder text of the chat input.                                                                                                             |\n67\t| `META VISIBILITY`                                        | Sets the [agent visibility](agents.md#visibility) from source.                                                                                  |\n68\t| `META VOICE` (`VOICE`)                                   | Voice used for TTS (see [Voice](chat/voice.md)).                                                                                                |\n69\t| `META DESCRIPTION` (`DESCRIPTION`)                       | Profile description override.                                                                                                                  |\n70\t| `MESSAGE`, `INITIAL MESSAGE`, `USER MESSAGE`, `AGENT MESSAGE`, `INTERNAL MESSAGE` | Scripted messages; `INITIAL MESSAGE` is shown when a chat starts.                                                     |\n71\t| `MESSAGE SUFFIX`                                         | Markdown appended to every agent reply (streamed after the model output; see [Streaming protocol](chat/streaming-protocol.md)).                  |\n72\t| `SCENARIO` / `SCENARIOS`                                 | Multi-step scripted scenarios.                                                                                                                  |\n73\t| `NOTE` / `NOTES` / `COMMENT` / `NONCE` / `TODO`          | Ignored by compilation (documentation only).                                                                                                    |\n74\t| `DELETE` / `CANCEL` / `DISCARD` / `REMOVE`               | Cancels a previously declared commitment.                                                                                                       |\n75\t| `DICTIONARY`                                             | Terminology definitions.                                                                                                                        |\n76\t| `OPEN`                                                   | Marks the book as openly self-improvable; carries teacher instructions (see [Self-learning](agents/self-learning.md)).                           |\n77\t| `CLOSED`                                                 | Locks the book against self-learning.                                                                                                           |\n78\t| `TEAM`                                                   | Declares teammate agents the agent can talk to (adds delegation tools; referenced as `{Agent Name}`; may cross servers).                         |\n79\t| `WALLET` / `WALLETS`                                     | Declares credentials the agent needs from the [user wallet](users/wallet.md).                                                                   |\n80\t| `USE BROWSER` (`BROWSER`)                                | Grants the web-browsing tool ([Runtime tools](chat/runtime-tools.md#run_browser)).                                                              |\n81\t| `USE SEARCH ENGINE` (`USE SEARCH`)                       | Grants web search.                                                                                                                              |\n82\t| `USE DEEPSEARCH`                                         | Grants deep research search.                                                                                                                    |\n83\t| `USE SPAWN` (`SPAWN`)                                    | Grants creating new agents ([spawn tool](chat/runtime-tools.md#spawn_agent)).                                                                    |\n84\t| `USE TIMEOUT`                                            | Grants scheduled wake-ups in durable chats ([Timeouts](chat/timeouts.md)).                                                                       |\n85\t| `USE TIME` (`TIME`, `DATE`, `CURRENT TIME`)              | Injects current date/time context.                                                                                                              |\n86\t| `USE USER LOCATION` (`USER LOCATION`)                    | Injects the user's location context.                                                                                                            |\n87\t| `USE CALENDAR` (`CALENDAR`)                              | Grants calendar tools ([Calendar](integrations/calendar.md)).                                                                                    |\n88\t| `USE EMAIL` (`EMAIL`, `MAIL`)                            | Grants email sending ([Email](integrations/email.md)).                                                                                           |\n89\t| `USE POPUP` (`POPUP`)                                    | Grants popup UI interactions.                                                                                                                    |\n90\t| `USE IMAGE GENERATOR`                                    | Grants image generation.                                                                                                                         |\n91\t| `USE MCP` (`MCP`)                                        | Connects external MCP servers as tools.                                                                                                          |\n92\t| `USE PRIVACY` (`PRIVACY`)                                | Privacy constraints on data handling.                                                                                                            |\n93\t| `USE PROJECT` (`PROJECT`)                                | Binds GitHub repositories ([GitHub projects](integrations/github-projects.md)).                                                                  |\n94\t| `EXPECT`, `BEHAVIOUR(S)`, `AVOID`, `AVOIDANCE`, `CONTEXT` | Reserved keywords — parsed but not yet implemented (MUST be accepted without error).                                                            |\n95\t\n96\t## Composition rules\n97\t\n98\t-   Later commitments generally **extend** the system message; for single-value settings (e.g. `META` types, `MODEL`) the **last occurrence wins**.\n99\t-   Commitment application is **ordered**: definitions are applied one by one in source order onto an initially empty requirements object.\n100\t-   Unknown leading-word lines are treated as plain content, not errors.\n101\t-   `computeAgentHash(agentSource)` MUST be deterministic over the exact source text — it is used for cache keys, history chains, and external service deduplication.\n102\t\n103\t## Documentation endpoint\n104\t\n105\t`GET /api/docs/book-language.md` returns the standalone Book-language documentation as `text/markdown`, dynamically generated so it always matches the commitments actually supported by the running server. The docs UI page (`/docs`) renders the same content (see [Pages](ui/pages.md#documentation)).\n106\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5fcf42d8-e79f-4895-8760-3d62c1e26adf","uuid":"edbcc3a8-07d3-4416-b762-b9c49b7e44d9","timestamp":"2026-07-07T15:22:58.067Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\me\\work\\ai\\promptbook\\specs\\book-language.md","content":"# Book Language\n\nThe **Book language** is the domain-specific language in which every agent's source (\"book\") is written. It is designed to be human-readable while expressing the full behavior of an agent — its \"soul\". This spec covers the language as the Agents Server consumes it; the authoritative end-user reference is generated by the server itself and served at `GET /api/docs/book-language.md` (with `GET /api/docs/book.md` as a backward-compatible alias). A compatible server MUST serve this documentation, generated from its commitment registry.\n\n## Source structure\n\n```book\nAgent Name\n\nPERSONA You are a helpful assistant that helps with cooking recipes.\nRULE Answer only questions about cooking.\nKNOWLEDGE https://example.com/recipes.pdf\nUSE SEARCH ENGINE Search only in French.\nMETA IMAGE https://example.com/avatar.png\n```\n\n-   **Line 1** is the agent name. When missing/empty, a default name is derived.\n-   A **commitment** starts with a recognized keyword at the beginning of a line and extends until the next commitment keyword or end of file (so a commitment's content may span multiple lines).\n-   The general pattern is `<KEYWORD> <content>`, e.g. `PERSONA You are…`, `USE SEARCH ENGINE Search only in French.`\n-   Text that belongs to no commitment is free-form persona text (part of the system-message composition).\n-   **Parameters** may appear anywhere in content: `@ParameterName` (single word) or `{parameter name}` / `{parameterName: description}`. They are substituted from prompt parameters at execution time.\n-   **Agent references** in commitment content use curly braces around an agent name or URL, e.g. `TEAM You can talk to {Criminal lawyer} and {https://other-server/agents/xyz}`.\n\n## Two-stage parsing\n\nA compatible implementation MUST provide both stages with the following division of labor:\n\n1. **`parseAgentSource` (synchronous, lightweight)** — extracts the [agent profile](agents.md#agent-profile) (name, hash, persona description, initial message, `meta` map, links, parameters, capabilities, samples, knowledge sources). It recognizes commitments syntactically, never performs I/O, and is used everywhere a profile is needed cheaply (listings, headers, routing).\n2. **`createAgentModelRequirements` (asynchronous)** — compiles the source into **agent model requirements** by applying each commitment definition in order. This may perform I/O (resolving referenced agents, knowledge indexing). Output shape:\n    -   `systemMessage` — the composed system prompt;\n    -   `userMessageSuffix` — optional text appended to user prompts;\n    -   `modelName` (and optional `temperature` and other model parameters);\n    -   `tools` — LLM tool definitions contributed by `USE …`/`TEAM`/`ACTION` commitments.\n\nThe server caches the compiled requirements per `agentHash` (`Agent.preparedModelRequirements`, see [Preparation and caching](agents/preparation-and-caching.md)) and exposes them for debugging via the [model-requirements API](api/public-agent-api.md#model-requirements).\n\n## Commitment registry\n\nThe commitment registry is the single source of truth for the language. Keywords are case-insensitive per definition below; singular/plural forms and listed aliases are equivalent. A compatible implementation MUST support:\n\n| Commitment (aliases)                                   | Effect                                                                                                                                        |\n| ------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `PERSONA` / `PERSONAE`                                   | Describes who the agent is; contributes to the system message (legacy fallback for the profile description).                                    |\n| `GOAL` / `GOALS`                                         | The agent's objective; the last one becomes the profile `personaDescription`.                                                                   |\n| `KNOWLEDGE`                                              | Attaches a knowledge source (URL, file) or inline knowledge; sources are indexed for retrieval (see [Preparation](agents/preparation-and-caching.md#knowledge-indexing)). |\n| `MEMORY` / `MEMORIES`                                    | Enables [user memory](users/memory.md) behavior.                                                                                                |\n| `RULE` / `RULES`                                         | Hard behavioral constraint in the system message.                                                                                               |\n| `STYLE` / `STYLES`                                       | Writing style instructions.                                                                                                                     |\n| `LANGUAGE` / `LANGUAGES`                                 | Response language constraint.                                                                                                                   |\n| `WRITING SAMPLE` / `WRITING RULES`                       | Style-by-example instructions.                                                                                                                  |\n| `SAMPLE` / `EXAMPLE`                                     | Example conversations (question/answer pairs surfaced in the profile).                                                                          |\n| `FORMAT` / `FORMATS`                                     | Output format constraints.                                                                                                                      |\n| `TEMPLATE` / `TEMPLATES`                                 | Response templates.                                                                                                                             |\n| `FROM`                                                   | Inheritance from a parent agent (see [Inheritance and imports](agents/inheritance-and-imports.md)). `FROM VOID` disables the implicit ancestor. |\n| `IMPORT` / `IMPORTS`                                     | Textual inclusion of another agent's source.                                                                                                    |\n| `MODEL` / `MODELS`                                       | Selects the LLM (and parameters like temperature).                                                                                              |\n| `ACTION` / `ACTIONS`                                     | Declares actions the agent can perform (tool-like).                                                                                             |\n| `COMPONENT`                                              | Declares UI components the agent may render.                                                                                                    |\n| `META <TYPE> <content>`                                  | Generic metadata; later same-type entries override earlier. Recognized types below.                                                             |\n| `META IMAGE` (`IMAGE`)                                   | Avatar/profile image URL (see [Avatars](agents/avatars-and-visuals.md)).                                                                        |\n| `META AVATAR`, `META VISUAL`                             | Built-in avatar visual identifier.                                                                                                              |\n| `META COLOR` (`COLOR`), `META FONT` (`FONT`)             | Brand color / font of the agent page.                                                                                                           |\n| `META LINK`                                              | Related links shown on the profile.                                                                                                             |\n| `META DOMAIN` (`DOMAIN`)                                 | Custom domain claim for the agent (see [Servers and multi-tenancy](servers-and-multi-tenancy.md#custom-domains)).                                |\n| `META DISCLAIMER`                                        | Markdown disclaimer users must accept before chatting (enforced; see [Public agent API](api/public-agent-api.md#meta-disclaimer)).               |\n| `META INPUT PLACEHOLDER`                                 | Placeholder text of the chat input.                                                                                                             |\n| `META VISIBILITY`                                        | Sets the [agent visibility](agents.md#visibility) from source.                                                                                  |\n| `META VOICE` (`VOICE`)                                   | Voice used for TTS (see [Voice](chat/voice.md)).                                                                                                |\n| `META DESCRIPTION` (`DESCRIPTION`)                       | Profile description override.                                                                                                                  |\n| `MESSAGE`, `INITIAL MESSAGE`, `USER MESSAGE`, `AGENT MESSAGE`, `INTERNAL MESSAGE` | Scripted messages; `INITIAL MESSAGE` is shown when a chat starts.                                                     |\n| `MESSAGE SUFFIX`                                         | Markdown appended to every agent reply (streamed after the model output; see [Streaming protocol](chat/streaming-protocol.md)).                  |\n| `SCENARIO` / `SCENARIOS`                                 | Multi-step scripted scenarios.                                                                                                                  |\n| `NOTE` / `NOTES` / `COMMENT` / `NONCE` / `TODO`          | Ignored by compilation (documentation only).                                                                                                    |\n| `DELETE` / `CANCEL` / `DISCARD` / `REMOVE`               | Cancels a previously declared commitment.                                                                                                       |\n| `DICTIONARY`                                             | Terminology definitions.                                                                                                                        |\n| `OPEN`                                                   | Marks the book as openly self-improvable; carries teacher instructions (see [Self-learning](agents/self-learning.md)).                           |\n| `CLOSED`                                                 | Locks the book against self-learning.                                                                                                           |\n| `TEAM`                                                   | Declares teammate agents the agent can talk to (adds delegation tools; referenced as `{Agent Name}`; may cross servers).                         |\n| `WALLET` / `WALLETS`                                     | Declares credentials the agent needs from the [user wallet](users/wallet.md).                                                                   |\n| `USE BROWSER` (`BROWSER`)                                | Grants the web-browsing tool ([Runtime tools](chat/runtime-tools.md#run_browser)).                                                              |\n| `USE SEARCH ENGINE` (`USE SEARCH`)                       | Grants web search.                                                                                                                              |\n| `USE DEEPSEARCH`                                         | Grants deep research search.                                                                                                                    |\n| `USE SPAWN` (`SPAWN`)                                    | Grants creating new agents ([spawn tool](chat/runtime-tools.md#spawn_agent)).                                                                    |\n| `USE TIMEOUT`                                            | Grants scheduled wake-ups in durable chats ([Timeouts](chat/timeouts.md)).                                                                       |\n| `USE TIME` (`TIME`, `DATE`, `CURRENT TIME`)              | Injects current date/time context.                                                                                                              |\n| `USE USER LOCATION` (`USER LOCATION`)                    | Injects the user's location context.                                                                                                            |\n| `USE CALENDAR` (`CALENDAR`)                              | Grants calendar tools ([Calendar](integrations/calendar.md)).                                                                                    |\n| `USE EMAIL` (`EMAIL`, `MAIL`)                            | Grants email sending ([Email](integrations/email.md)).                                                                                           |\n| `USE POPUP` (`POPUP`)                                    | Grants popup UI interactions.                                                                                                                    |\n| `USE IMAGE GENERATOR`                                    | Grants image generation.                                                                                                                         |\n| `USE MCP` (`MCP`)                                        | Connects external MCP servers as tools.                                                                                                          |\n| `USE PRIVACY` (`PRIVACY`)                                | Privacy constraints on data handling.                                                                                                            |\n| `USE PROJECT` (`PROJECT`)                                | Binds GitHub repositories ([GitHub projects](integrations/github-projects.md)).                                                                  |\n| `EXPECT`, `BEHAVIOUR(S)`, `AVOID`, `AVOIDANCE`, `CONTEXT` | Reserved keywords — parsed but not yet implemented (MUST be accepted without error).                                                            |\n\n## Composition rules\n\n-   Later commitments generally **extend** the system message; for single-value settings (e.g. `META` types, `MODEL`) the **last occurrence wins**.\n-   Commitment application is **ordered**: definitions are applied one by one in source order onto an initially empty requirements object.\n-   Unknown leading-word lines are treated as plain content, not errors.\n-   `computeAgentHash(agentSource)` MUST be deterministic over the exact source text — it is used for cache keys, history chains, and external service deduplication.\n\n## Documentation endpoint\n\n`GET /api/docs/book-language.md` returns the standalone Book-language documentation as `text/markdown`, dynamically generated so it always matches the commitments actually supported by the running server. The docs UI page (`/docs`) renders the same content (see [Pages](ui/pages.md#documentation)).\n","numLines":106,"startLine":1,"totalLines":106}}}
